     9→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:08Z", "finding_type": "software", "source_url": "https://ssginsight.com/industries/light-rail-transport/", "content": "Agility CMMS (SSG Insight): Cloud-based EAM/CMMS. Used by Keolis Amey Metrolink (UK's largest light railway). Nottingham Trams reduced failure downtime from average 10 days to 1 day after implementation.", "relevance": "high"}
    10→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:09Z", "finding_type": "software", "source_url": "https://stefanini.com/en/insights/articles/the-implementation-and-development-of-a-complex-cmms-system-for-maintenance-in-transportation-industry", "content": "IBM Maximo and CARL Source: Used for complex railway/metro maintenance. CARL Source notable for flexibility and customizability, streamlines maintenance operations, reduces downtime.", "relevance": "high"}
    11→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:10Z", "finding_type": "software", "source_url": "https://mobility-work.com/blog/reliable-railway-maintenance/", "content": "Mobility Work: Next Gen Maintenance Management platform for all train types, railway systems (electrification, communications, AC, depot equipment). Can deploy for maintenance, fleet management, spare parts, purchasing, operations.", "relevance": "medium"}
    12→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:11Z", "finding_type": "software", "source_url": "https://www.ibm.com/products/maximo/travel-transportation", "content": "IBM Maximo Application Suite (MAS): Asset lifecycle management for travel/transportation including airports, aviation, rail, fleet. Uses AI/ML to forecast component failures on railcars, tracks, switches. Real-time condition monitoring, advanced simulations for wear/tear analysis.", "relevance": "high"}
    13→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:12Z", "finding_type": "software", "source_url": "https://www.ibm.com/docs/en/mft/7.6.2?topic=product-overview", "content": "IBM Maximo for Transportation: Consist Management feature allows managing train configurations (locomotives, wagons) to schedule and perform maintenance for all cars in that configuration. Vital for railway assets and rail vehicles.", "relevance": "high"}
    14→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:13Z", "finding_type": "approach", "source_url": "https://asean.newsroom.ibm.com/SBS-Transit-Taps-IBM", "content": "SBS Transit Singapore (Nov 2024): First Asia-Pacific implementation integrating IBM Maximo with generative AI for rail operations. Enhances asset management with AI technology.", "relevance": "medium"}
    15→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:14Z", "finding_type": "approach", "source_url": "https://www.eweek.com/networking/ibm-maximo-software-used-in-three-railroad-projects/", "content": "Major US transit using Maximo: Long Island Rail Road (NY), BART San Francisco (346k passengers/day - monitors assets, schedules maintenance, manages inventory), Metro Washington DC. Las Vegas Monorail upgraded Maximo 4.0.3 to 7.6 for lower costs and higher reliability.", "relevance": "high"}
    16→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:15Z", "finding_type": "approach", "source_url": "https://www.rail-services.it/en/preventive-maintenance-of-rolling-stock/", "content": "Three maintenance approaches: (1) Time/Cyclical - interventions at regular intervals based on schedule/hours/cycles/km, (2) Condition-based - continuous monitoring of temperature, vibrations, pressure, oil via sensors, intervene only at critical conditions, (3) Predictive - using latest technologies.", "relevance": "high"}
    17→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:16Z", "finding_type": "approach", "source_url": "http://www.railway-technical.com/trains/train-maintenance/", "content": "Rolling stock is most maintenance-intensive part of railway. Reliability is key - stalled train blocks railway immediately. In high-speed train lifecycle, maintenance = 30% of life costs (similar for other train types).", "relevance": "high"}
    18→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:17Z", "finding_type": "approach", "source_url": "https://www.brainkart.com/article/Maintenance-of-Coaches-and-Wagons_4332/", "content": "Typical maintenance intervals: Coach lifespan 30 years, wagon 40 years. Periodic Overhaul (POH) frequency: 12-24 months depending on service type. Vacuum brakes: 18 months for coaching stock, 18-24 months for goods stock.", "relevance": "high"}
    19→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:18Z", "finding_type": "approach", "source_url": "https://www.mpofcinci.com/blog/train-maintenance-schedule-best-practices/", "content": "Modern short-term scheduling: Work scheduled for all units with maintenance due in 3-week horizon. Inputs: predicted due dates, required resources, tooling knowledge. Schedules customized from OEM guidelines based on duty cycles.", "relevance": "high"}
    20→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:19Z", "finding_type": "approach", "source_url": "https://clickup.com/p/gantt-chart-software/railway-technician", "content": "Gantt chart visualization for railway: Visualize each step from diagnostics to completion, use templates/dependencies for consistency, assign roles and deadlines. Enables shift transitions, quick timeline adjustments for urgent issues.", "relevance": "high"}
    21→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:20Z", "finding_type": "challenge", "source_url": "https://railquip.com/blog/railroad-trends/railway-maintenance-problems/", "content": "Challenge: Railroad tracks extend hundreds of miles, constant inspection/maintenance difficult. Exception conditions cause damage requiring urgent attention. Juggling limited resources from planned schedules for urgent needs impacts proactive inspection capability.", "relevance": "high"}
    22→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:21Z", "finding_type": "challenge", "source_url": "https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0968090X21001273", "content": "Challenge: Maintenance and train operations are mutually exclusive. Determining maintenance work slots vs train operation paths is inherently problematic. High-traffic lines face critical planning conflicts. Research historically focused more on train operations than infrastructure maintenance.", "relevance": "high"}
    23→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:22Z", "finding_type": "challenge", "source_url": "https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0191261521001284", "content": "Challenge: Locomotive Scheduling Problem (LSP) - assigning fleet to scheduled trains while minimizing costs. Rolling stock is main cost driver, must maximize utilization. Special maintenance constraints significantly increase computational difficulty.", "relevance": "high"}
    24→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:23Z", "finding_type": "challenge", "source_url": "https://www.tektracking.com/key-challenges-of-track-maintenance-and-how-to-resolve-them/", "content": "Challenge: Communication and coordination - railways are vast inter-dependent networks. Efficient inspection/maintenance requires robust communication within track department AND collaboration with other departments. Highly time-sensitive.", "relevance": "high"}
    25→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:24Z", "finding_type": "challenge", "source_url": "https://adortech.com/blog/challenges-and-innovations-in-railroad-maintenance", "content": "Challenge: Climate change impact - snow, extreme heat, storms, cold winters harm rail infrastructure safety. Must be considered when initiating maintenance planning.", "relevance": "medium"}
    26→{"task_id": "TASK-020", "timestamp": "2026-01-06T10:00:25Z", "finding_type": "approach", "source_url": "https://adortech.com/blog/railway-infrastructure-maintenance", "content": "Solution: Proactive track inspection tools providing real-time data on conditions. Enables predictable schedules. Asset management systems fed by usage metrics, tonnage reports, climate data, component lifespans. Proactive repairs far more cost-effective than reactive fixes.", "relevance": "high"}
